H0.text: In Greek mythology who was the god of the north winds. Zephyr

H1.text: In Greek mythology who was the god of the north winds. Notus

H2.text: In Greek mythology who was the god of the north winds. Eurus

H3.text: In Greek mythology who was the god of the north winds. Boreas

A4.text: Boreas is the Greek god of the cold north wind, storms, and winter.

A5.text: Roman writers Aulus Gellius and Pliny the Elder took Boreas as a northeast wind, equivalent to the Roman god Aquilo or Septentrio.
